
# Hugging Face Space Configuration for AI-Enhanced Translation
# Get your space URL from: https://huggingface.co/spaces

# Production Environment Variable
# NOTE: Provide ONLY the base space URL without /api/predict - the service will add it automatically
VITE_HUGGINGFACE_SPACE_URL=https://your-space-url.hf.space

# Groq API Configuration (Optional - for advanced features)
# Get your API key from: https://console.groq.com
VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 
# For Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace 'https://your-space-url.hf.space' with your actual Hugging Face Space URL
#    IMPORTANT: Use ONLY the base URL (e.g., https://josebert-ibi-voice-backend.hf.space)
#    DO NOT include /api/predict - the service will add it automatically
# 3. Optionally add your Groq API key for advanced features
# 4. The application will automatically use these for AI features
#
# For Production Deployment (Vercel):
# 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add VITE_HUGGINGFACE_SPACE_URL with your base space URL (without /api/predict)
# 4. Optionally add VITE_GROQ_API_KEY for advanced features
# 5. Set for Production, Preview, and Development environments
# 6. Redeploy your application
#
# For Other Hosting Platforms:
# Set VITE_HUGGINGFACE_SPACE_URL as an environment variable with the base URL only
#
# URL Format Examples:
# ✅ Correct: https://josebert-ibi-voice-backend.hf.space
# ❌ Wrong: https://josebert-ibi-voice-backend.hf.space/api/predict
#
# Security Note:
# Never commit .env.local or any file containing actual API keys to your repository
# Always use environment variables for production deployments
